ClassDecl.Name: GuiListControl
ClassDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Represents a list control. A list control automatically read data sources and creates corresponding data item control from the item template.</summary> </Document>

ClassDecl.Name: IItemProviderCallback
ClassDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Item provider callback. Item providers use this interface to notify item modification.</summary> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: OnAttached
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Called when an item provider callback object is attached to an item provider.</summary> <param name="provider">The item provider.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: OnItemModified
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Called when items in the item provider is modified.</summary> <param name="start">The index of the first modified item.</param> <param name="count">The number of all modified items.</param> <param name="newCount">The number of new items. If items are inserted or removed, newCount may not equals to count.</param> </Document>

ClassDecl.Name: IItemArrangerCallback
ClassDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Item arranger callback. Item arrangers use this interface to communicate with the list control. When setting positions for item controls, functions in this callback object is suggested to call because they use the result from the <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::compositions::IGuiAxis@s:vl.presentation.compositions.IGuiAxis" /></links>.</summary> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: RequestItem
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Request an item control representing an item in the item provider. This function is suggested to call when an item control gets into the visible area.</summary> <returns>The item control.</returns> <param name="itemIndex">The index of the item in the item provider.</param> <param name="itemComposition">The composition that represents the item. Set to null if the item style is expected to be put directly into the list control.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: ReleaseItem
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Release an item control. This function is suggested to call when an item control gets out of the visible area.</summary> <param name="style">The item control.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetViewLocation
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Update the view location. The view location is the left-top position in the logic space of the list control.</summary> <param name="value">The new view location.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetStylePreferredSize
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the preferred size of an item control.</summary> <returns>The preferred size of an item control.</returns> <param name="style">The item control.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetStyleAlignmentToParent
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Set the alignment of an item control.</summary> <param name="style">The item control.</param> <param name="margin">The new alignment.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetStyleBounds
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the bounds of an item control.</summary> <returns>The bounds of an item control.</returns> <param name="style">The item control.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetStyleBounds
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Set the bounds of an item control.</summary> <param name="style">The item control.</param> <param name="bounds">The new bounds.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetContainerComposition
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::compositions::GuiGraphicsComposition@s:vl.presentation.compositions.GuiGraphicsComposition" /></links> that directly contains item controls.</summary> <returns>The <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::compositions::GuiGraphicsComposition@s:vl.presentation.compositions.GuiGraphicsComposition" /></links> that directly contains item controls.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: OnTotalSizeChanged
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Notify the list control that the total size of all item controls are changed.</summary> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: AttachCallback
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Attach an item provider callback to this item provider.</summary> <returns>Returns true if this operation succeeded.</returns> <param name="value">The item provider callback.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: DetachCallback
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Detach an item provider callback from this item provider.</summary> <returns>Returns true if this operation succeeded.</returns> <param name="value">The item provider callback.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: PushEditing
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Increase the editing counter indicating that an <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::templates::GuiListItemTemplate@s:vl.presentation.templates.GuiListItemTemplate" /></links> is editing an item.</summary> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: PopEditing
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Decrease the editing counter indicating that an <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::templates::GuiListItemTemplate@s:vl.presentation.templates.GuiListItemTemplate" /></links> has stopped editing an item.</summary> <returns>Returns false if there is no supression before calling this function.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: IsEditing
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Test if an <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::templates::GuiListItemTemplate@s:vl.presentation.templates.GuiListItemTemplate" /></links> is editing an item.</summary> <returns>Returns false if there is no editing.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: Count
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the number of items in this item proivder.</summary> <returns>The number of items in this item proivder.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetTextValue
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the text representation of an item.</summary> <returns>The text representation of an item.</returns> <param name="itemIndex">The index of the item.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetBindingValue
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the binding value of an item.</summary> <returns>The binding value of an item.</returns> <param name="itemIndex">The index of the item.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: RequestView
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Request a view for this item provider. If the specified view is not supported, it returns null. If you want to get a view of type IXXX, use IXXX::Identifier as the identifier.</summary> <returns>The view object.</returns> <param name="identifier">The identifier for the requested view.</param> </Document>

ClassDecl.Name: IItemArranger
ClassDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Item arranger for a <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::controls::GuiListControl@s:vl.presentation.controls.GuiListControl" /></links>. Item arranger decides how to arrange and item controls. When implementing an item arranger, <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::controls::GuiListControl::IItemArrangerCallback@s:vl.presentation.controls.GuiListControl" /></links> is suggested to use when calculating locations and sizes for item controls.</summary> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: AttachListControl
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Called when an item arranger in installed to a <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::controls::GuiListControl@s:vl.presentation.controls.GuiListControl" /></links>.</summary> <param name="value">The list control.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: DetachListControl
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Called when an item arranger in uninstalled from a <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::controls::GuiListControl@s:vl.presentation.controls.GuiListControl" /></links>.</summary> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetCallback
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the binded item arranger callback object.</summary> <returns>The binded item arranger callback object.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetCallback
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Bind the item arranger callback object.</summary> <param name="value">The item arranger callback object to bind.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetTotalSize
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the total size of all data controls.</summary> <returns>The total size.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetVisibleStyle
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the item style controller for an visible item index. If an item is not visible, it returns null.</summary> <returns>The item style controller.</returns> <param name="itemIndex">The item index.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetVisibleIndex
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the item index for an visible item style controller. If an item is not visible, it returns -1.</summary> <returns>The item index.</returns> <param name="style">The item style controller.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: ReloadVisibleStyles
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Reload all visible items.</summary> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: OnViewChanged
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Called when the visible area of item container is changed.</summary> <param name="bounds">The new visible area.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: FindItem
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Find the item by an base item and a key direction.</summary> <returns>The item index that is found. Returns -1 if this operation failed.</returns> <param name="itemIndex">The base item index.</param> <param name="key">The key direction.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: EnsureItemVisible
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Adjust the view location to make an item visible.</summary> <returns>Returns true if this operation succeeded.</returns> <param name="itemIndex">The item index of the item to be made visible.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetAdoptedSize
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the adopted size for the view bounds.</summary> <returns>The adopted size, making the vids bounds just enough to display several items.</returns> <param name="expectedSize">The expected size, to provide a guidance.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GuiListControl
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Create a control with a specified style provider.</summary> <param name="themeName">The theme name for retriving a default control template.</param> <param name="_itemProvider">The item provider as a data source.</param> <param name="acceptFocus">Set to true if the list control is allowed to have a keyboard focus.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Test if the list control displays predefined item background.</summary> <returns>Returns true if the list control displays predefined item background.</returns> </Document>
